.TH "ibmvmc_return_hmc" 9 "ibmvmc_return_hmc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ibmvmc_return_hmc \- Return an HMC Connection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ibmvmc_return_hmc
.BI "(struct ibmvmc_hmc *hmc "  ","
.BI "bool release_readers "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hmc" 12
ibmvmc_hmc struct
.IP "release_readers" 12
Number of readers connected to session
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function releases the HMC connections back into the pool.
.SH "RETURN"
0 - Success
Non-zero - Failure
